defaultTAKING ACTION WHEN A REGISTRANT’S FTP FALLS BELOW STANDARDS
defaultMeeting the HCPC’s Burden of Proof – Evidence Given Based on Personal Interaction
defaultThe HCPC lay claim to 
defaultrobust governance arrangements, defaultoveralldefault effective casework systems and efficient business processesdefault. 
defaultAllegations 
defaultAllegations were revised seven months 
defaultAFTER
default ICP agreement and 
defaultAFTER ALL
default&#xa0;
defaultevidence had been gathered from both sides.  These amended allegations were accepted by a CCC on the day of a hearing. This process was considered to be ‘fair’ to better reflect the HCPC’s burden of proof.  The HCPC considers a CCC to have an 
defaultinherent powerdefault to undertake this process.
