defaultDocumentary Evidence Handling
defaultThe HCPC omitted from the investigation process and failed to disclose to the proceedings critical, exculpatory documentary evidence in the form of 
defaultPatient Care Recordsdefault,  claiming the disclosure of this evidence to be ‘desirable’ but not ‘essential’ to fulfill their burden of proof.  A 
defaultdishonestdefault written statement made by the HCPC exists that states this evidence is no longer available when it is in fact in their possession.
