default “Of the 100 cases audited, we identified 31 cases in which we had 
defaultconcerns around risk assessments and defaultcompliance with the HCPC’s operational guidancedefault.default 
defaultMore specifically, we found 27 cases (including cases closed by HCPC staff and following an ICP decision) where risk assessments had not been completed at all required stages in the process.
defaultConducting a robust risk assessment on receipt of a new complaint and updating that risk assessment in light of new information is an important part of public protection within a risk-based regulatory approach. 
defaultUnless the regulator has conducted a proper evaluation of risk, it is difficult to make sound defaultjudgementsdefault defaultabout whether any regulatory action is necessary,”
defaultWe recommend that the HCPC reviews our findings in these cases and considers whether improvements can be made to its processes and procedures to defaultminimisedefault the risk of any of the issues highlighted above reoccurring in the future.defaultIn response to this external audit, the HCPC published:
