defaultNHS staff are not to blame, in the vast majority of cases it is the systems, procedures, conditions, environment and constraints that they face that lead to patient safety problems.  defaultWell intentioned people who make errors or are involved in systems that have failed around them need to be supported, not punished.default  defaultGenuine errors are not misconduct and do not warrant punishmentdefault?default&#xa0;
